{{Quote|I'm going to need to see further identification."''<br />''"It's all there, Sergeant. I'm a member in good standing of the Republic Senate."''<br />''"So it says. But I'm still going to need to see further identification.|A clone shock trooper talking with Bail Organa at a Homeworld Security checkpoint|<ref name="LabEvil">''[[Labyrinth of Evil]]''</ref>}}
'''Homeworld Security Command''', or simply '''Homeworld Security''', was a branch of the [[Galactic Republic/Legends|Galactic Republic]] charged with ensuring the security of the [[Capital/Legends|capital]] [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Coruscant/Legends|Coruscant]]. This included coordinating security patrols and managing [[Orbital security station/Legends|orbital security stations]] with [[Republic Military/Legends|military]] forces, as well as keeping them on alert for security threats to Coruscant. During the [[Clone Wars/Legends|Clone Wars]] between the Republic and the [[Confederacy of Independent Systems/Legends|Confederacy of Independent Systems]], the [[Clone shock trooper/Legends|clone shock troopers]] of the [[Coruscant Guard/Legends|Coruscant Guard]] were assigned to Homeworld Security Command to enforce tightening security measures. Stationed outside public gathering areas such as theaters, [[Hotel/Legends|hotels]], government buildings and other areas of vital infrastructure, the shock [[Trooper/Legends|troopers]] were given wide powers to stop and search beings, their belongings, and private residences. Although most citizens of Coruscant saw no issue with the measures, certain [[Senator/Legends|Senators]] such as [[Bail Prestor Organa/Legends|Bail Organa]] did. Recognizing that the shock [[Troop/Legends|troopers]] were simply responding to their training, Organa still saw the actions of the troopers as another method for [[Supreme Chancellor/Legends|Supreme Chancellor]] [[Palpatine/Legends|Palpatine]] to grab power. Despite the increase in security, Homeworld Security was still caught off guard when [[General/Legends|General]] [[Grievous/Legends|Grievous]] of the Separatists [[Battle of Coruscant/Legends|attacked]] Coruscant and kidnapped Chancellor Palpatine. With the [[Declaration of a New Order]] establishing the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire]], shock troopers were stationed in the [[Senate Building/Legends|Senate Building]] and [[Republic Executive Building/Legends|Republic Executive Building]] to ensure a smooth transition of government.

==Description==
[[File:CloneShockTrooper-TSWB.png|thumb|right|120px|Coruscant Guards were the most visible element of Homeworld Security.]]
{{Quote|They're competent at defense. They're not used to attacking.|GAR Clone Captain Ordo discussing Coruscant law enforcement|<ref name="TripleZero">''[[Republic Commando: Triple Zero]]''</ref>}}
Homeworld Security Command was a branch of the [[Galactic Republic/Legends|Galactic Republic]] charged with coordinating security operations on the [[Capital/Legends|capital]] [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Coruscant/Legends|Coruscant]]. Composed of a civilian team, Homeworld Security worked closely with [[Republic Military/Legends|military]] forces to ensure that [[Orbital security station/Legends|orbital security stations]] and ground-based security patrols were on alert for any major security threats.<ref name="CSWEhsc" /> They set up emergency procedures and coordinated responses to major security incidents. During the [[Clone Wars/Legends|Clone Wars]] between the Republic and the [[Confederacy of Independent Systems/Legends|Confederacy of Independent Systems]], Homeworld Security supervised the [[Coruscant Guard/Legends|Coruscant Guard]],<ref name="LabEvil" /> an elite<ref name="CCFox">{{SWE|characters|clone-commander-fox|Clone Commander Fox}}</ref> body composed of [[Clone shock trooper/Legends|clone shock troopers]]<ref name="LabEvil" /> under the command of the fiercely loyal and highly decorated [[Clone Commander/Legends|Clone Commander]] [[Fox/Legends|Fox]]. As Homeworld Security personnel,<ref name="CCFox" /> the [[Trooper/Legends|troopers]] were stationed outside major businesses, government buildings, and other public areas to conduct checkpoints. The Guards also conducted police raids and searches and seizures of any suspicious persons.<ref name="LabEvil" />

==History==
{{Quote|Alert Homeworld Security that General Grievous has broken through the perimeter.|Shaak Ti to Armand Isard|<ref name="LabEvil" />}}
To ensure public safety, Homeworld Security coordinated their efforts with civilian [[Law enforcement agency/Legends|police]] and military forces. They were active by [[22 BBY/Legends|22 BBY]] with the [[First Battle of Geonosis/Legends|outbreak]] of the Clone Wars between the Republic and the Confederacy of Independent Systems<ref name="CSWEhsc" /> when incidents of [[Terrorist/Legends|terrorism]] and the threat of invasion became a pressing concern. A successful anti-terror [[Mission to Coruscant (Clone Wars)|operation]] by [[Clone commando/Legends|clone commandos]] of the [[Grand Army of the Republic/Legends|Grand Army of the Republic's]] [[Special Operations Brigade/Legends|Special Operations Brigade]] and members of the [[Anti-Terrorism Unit]] of the [[Coruscant Security Force/Legends|Coruscant Security Force]] (CSF) demonstrated the need and usefulness of [[Clone trooper/Legends|clone troopers]] to assist in securing Coruscant.<ref name="TripleZero" />

As part of increased efforts to tighten security, the [[Cloning/Legends|clone]] shock [[Troop/Legends|troopers]] were established as the [[Coruscant Guard/Legends|Coruscant Guard]]<ref name="CSWEcoreguard">{{CSWECite|I|147&ndash;148|Coruscant Guard}}</ref> and became a part of Homeworld Security.<ref name="LabEvil" /> Although unknown at the [[Time/Legends|time]] by the general public, the move had been pre-planned by [[Supreme Chancellor/Legends|Supreme Chancellor]] [[Palpatine/Legends|Palpatine]].<ref name="SW:DP">[[Darth Plagueis (novel)|''Darth Plagueis'']]</ref> The shock [[Trooper/Legends|troopers]], as well as the clones of the [[501st Legion/Legends|501st Legion]], had been trained on Coruscant for law enforcement duties and emerged trained for the [[City/Legends|city]] terrain with the outbreak of war.<ref name="CSWEthire">{{CSWECite|III|237|Thire, Clone Commander}}</ref> The passage of the [[Emergency Powers Act/Legends|Emergency Powers Act]] by the [[Galactic Senate/Legends|Galactic Senate]] and, later into the war, the [[Enhanced Security and Enforcement Act]], gave Homeworld Security increased authority to secure Coruscant. Shock troopers operated increased checkpoints and were stationed at vital government buildings, banks, [[Hotel/Legends|hotels]], theaters, and other major gathering areas. The shock troopers had authority to conduct stops and search beings as well as search belongings and private residences. Other measures by Homeworld Security including having [[Holocamera/Legends|Holocams]] installed in previously private areas of the Senate's [[Grand Convocation Chamber]]. Rumors surfaced of other government activities, such as antiwar demonstrations put down with brutal force, beings disappearing, and private property seized from their owners, although they were quickly discredited by government officials. [[Senator/Legends|Senator]] [[Bail Prestor Organa/Legends|Bail Organa]] recognized the actions of the shock troopers as those of bred [[Soldier/Legends|soldiers]] simply following their training and that there was no randomness or animosity in their actions. Yet Organa and other senators felt that the deeds of the shock troopers were just more examples of too much power resting in the hands of Palpatine, whom they viewed as the driving force behind Homeworld Security.<ref name="LabEvil" />

[[File:Secforce.jpg|thumb|left|250px|Homeworld Security coordinated activities between the police and military.]]
Despite the increased security measures and coordination between military and civilian forces, Homeworld Security was caught off guard with the [[Battle of Coruscant/Legends|attack]] on Coruscant by the Separatist [[General/Legends|General]] [[Grievous/Legends|Grievous]]. As [[Coruscant Command HQ|Coruscant military command]] coordinated defense efforts with the [[Coruscant Defense Fleet/Legends|Coruscant Home Fleet]] and the arriving [[Open Circle Fleet/Legends|Open Circle Fleet]], Homeworld Security enacted its emergency procedures.<ref name="LabEvil" /> The CSF attempted to evacuate vulnerable areas and clear [[Skylane/Legends|skylanes]] as Separatist [[Battle droid/Legends|battle droids]] landed and fought with Republic clone troopers.<ref name="Order66">''[[Order 66: A Republic Commando Novel]]''</ref> Supreme Chancellor Palpatine and his [[Red Guard]]s were moved from the Senate Building and secured at [[500 Republica/Legends|500 Republica]]. However, those measures were unable to prevent Grievous from landing and kidnapping the Chancellor, overwhelming Palpatine's security detail.<ref name="LabEvil" /> Two [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]], [[Jedi Master/Legends|Master]] [[Obi-Wan Kenobi/Legends|Obi-Wan Kenobi]] and [[Jedi Knight/Legends|Jedi Knight]] [[Anakin Skywalker/Legends|Anakin Skywalker]], retrieved the Chancellor, and Republic forces routed the Separatists. In the aftermath of the battle, the presence of Coruscant Guard shock troopers and the 501st Legion were increased in public areas on Coruscant. Clone troopers were also paired with CSF [[Police officer/Legends|police officers]] on patrol and checkpoints were increased.<ref name="Order66" />

Palpatine's issuance of [[Order 66/Legends|Order 66]], which declared all [[Jedi Order/Legends|Jedi]] as enemies of the state, became a major operation of Homeworld Security. As the 501st Legion under the command of the new [[Dark Lord of the Sith/Legends|Dark Lord of the Sith]] [[Anakin Skywalker/Legends|Darth Vader]] [[Operation: Knightfall/Legends|took]] the [[Jedi Temple/Legends|Jedi Temple]], the [[Office of the Supreme Chancellor/Legends|Chancellor's office]] declared martial law.<ref name="SWE3book">[[Star Wars: Revenge of the Sith (novelization)|''Star Wars'': Episode III ''Revenge of the Sith'' novelization]]</ref> With Palpatine's [[Declaration of a New Order]], in which he dissolved the Republic and claimed the title of [[Galactic Emperor/Legends|Galactic Emperor]], the Coruscant Guard was stationed in the Senate Building and [[Republic Executive Building/Legends|Republic Executive Building]] to ensure a smooth transition of government.<ref name="CSWEthire" /> The reorganization of the Republic into the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire]] brought drastic changes. With the new [[Imperial Military/Legends|military]] authority in place, the Coruscant Guard became independent and was given primacy to police Coruscant,<ref name="GalaxyWar">''[[Galaxy at War]]''</ref> although they continued to rely on the Coruscant Security Force for general support.<ref name="Betrayal">''[[Star Wars: Empire: Betrayal]]''</ref> The [[Internal Security Bureau/Legends|Internal Security Bureau]] had already been formed<ref name="CSWEisb">{{CSWECite|II|96|Imperial Security Bureau}}</ref> and was combined with elements of the [[Commission for the Protection of the Republic/Legends|Commission for the Protection of the Republic]] and CSF's Anti-Terrorism and [[Detective/Legends|detective]] divisions by order of Palpatine. They became the [[Imperial Security Bureau/Legends|Imperial Security Bureau]] (ISB) which took a firm grip in all issues related to internal and external security threats.<ref name="501st">''[[Imperial Commando: 501st]]''</ref>

==Behind the scenes==
{{Quote|Some readers have accused me of including President Bush in the mix, but this is not the case. I borrowed the term "Homeworld Security" from one of the Dark Horse ''Republic'' comics, and my play on "Axis of Evil" was not an attempt to draw parallels between Bush and Palpatine, but to pay light-hearted homage to what I consider a very interesting phrase.|James Luceno|<ref name="Clone Warz">{{WebCite|url=http://www.clonewarz.com/features/interviews/luceno.htm|text=JAMES LUCENO INTERVIEW|author=[[Nathan O'Keefe]]|date=2005-04|work=[https://web.archive.org/web/20061129083714/http://www.clonewarz.com The Unofficial Clone Wars Site]|archivedate=20061115060448|nolive=1}}</ref>}}
[[File:Scribeluceno.jpg|thumb|right|300px|While commentators drew a connection between Homeworld Security Command and the newly established U.S. Department of Homeland Security, author James Luceno (pictured) claimed that was not his personal intention.]]
Homeworld Security Command first appeared in ''[[Labyrinth of Evil]]'', a novel written by [[James Luceno]] and published on [[January 25]], [[2005]]. Homeworld Security also received an entry in ''[[The Complete Star Wars Encyclopedia]]'', published in [[2008]] by [[Del Rey]]. Reviewers of ''Labyrinth of Evil'' made note of several similarities between the novel and the real world. One such alleged connection is that the Homeworld Security Command and the new security procedures have a striking resemblance to the real-world [[Wikipedia:United States Department of Homeland Security|U.S. Department of Homeland Security]],<ref name="bookreview">{{WebCite|url=http://theforce.net/books/reviews/r_labyrinthofevil.asp|text=TheForce.Net ''Labyrinth of Evil'' book review|work=[[TheForce.net]]|archivedate=20190730111457}}</ref> a department set up to combat terrorist threats.<ref name="DHS">{{WebCite|url=https://www.dhs.gov/about-dhs|text=About DHS (Department of Homeland Security wesite)|work=[[Wikipedia:United States Department of Homeland Security|United States Department of Homeland Security]]|archivedate=20200417085612}}</ref> Luceno claimed that it was not his intention to draw parallels between Palpatine and the [[Wikipedia:Presidency of George W. Bush|then-current Bush Administration]], claiming he had found the term "Homeworld Security" from the ''[[Star Wars: Republic]]'' comic line.<ref name="Clone Warz" />

Homeworld Security's fate after the formation of the Empire has not been officially clarified. ''The Complete Star Wars Encyclopedia'' lists Homeworld Security Command as a Republic organization but makes no mention of its status during the Empire. Other sources indicate Homeworld Security's responsibilities were given to other agencies. As stated in ''[[Galaxy at War]]'', law enforcement functions and coordinating the activities of police and military forces on Coruscant came under the Coruscant Guard and the Emperor's Royal Guard with the Coruscant Security Force in a support capacity. The responsibility to monitor for internal and external threats was given to the Imperial Security Bureau according to ''The Complete Star Wars Encyclopedia'' and numerous other sources, including ''[[Imperial Commando: 501st]]''.

